Human foamy virus (HFV) is a retrovirus encoding structural genes and, like 
human immunodeficiency virus and human T cell leukemia virus I, several 
ancillary reading frames collectively termed the be1 genes. We have previously 
shown that HFV transgenic mice develop an encephalopathy with neuronal loss in 
hippocampus and cerebral cortex. We have now raised and characterized rabbit 
antisera to various recombinant portions of gag, pol, env, and bel-1, the viral 
