transgenic mice coexpressing full-length HFV genes but not in mice expressing 
truncated gag and env, suggesting that these genes contain a fusogenic domain. 
Expression of full-length structural genes decreased the life expectancy of 
transgenic mice, implying an adjuvant role for these proteins in HFV-induced 
brain damage.

